result.execSummary:
The defendant Brian Keith Young was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brian Keith Young is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brian Keith Young was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Brian Keith Young not in court.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per email from Probation Dept., defendant is currently in absconder status.  Court ordered defendant to serve 45 days of the condition time; straight time.  Commitment For Condition Time For Non-Compliance With Probation Conditions - Domestic Violence Court signed and filed.

Defendant Brian Keith Young in court with attorney Angel Lee Johnson.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 90 days in the House of Correction, with credit for 3 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 45 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-No contact with victim Lakeitha P. unless approved by the agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay the DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Court WAIVED all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-Provide DNA Sample.

Filed: 
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief
-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation

Probation Review Hearing in Branch 24.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for August 26, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Brian Keith Young in court with attorney Angel Lee Johnson.  Benjamin Calvin Verhulst appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Case set for Jury Trial. State unable to proceed on count 1. On motion of the state, court DISMISSED count 1 without prejudice. Parties have reached a resolution on remaining charge. 

AS TO COUNT 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to NO CONTEST. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence. 

Case adjourned to branch 24 for Sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed, Defense Motion in Limine.
Received and Filed, State's Witness List.

Defendant Brian Keith Young in court with attorney Angel Lee Johnson.  Sarah Zwach appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Case heard off the record. Final Pretrial held. Parties ready to proceed to trial, neither party requests to address the court on the record. Signed, Filed & Distributed, Agreed Upon Request for A New Court Date form. Case remains scheduled for Jury Trial on 4/20/2016 at 8:30 am. Case adjourned to branch 24.

Jury trial scheduled for April 20, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Brian Keith Young in court.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance.  Defendant IS Public Defender eligible.  Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  The case is adjourned to Br. 24 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 19, 2016 at 08:30 am.
